A research note was distributed to all individuals involved in
Support analyses relative to testing of # 1725 cigarettes with and
without 7 mm filter cavities. These cavities were filled with a
range of materials from coconut charcoal to charcoal with bovine
hemoglobin (2:1) to 100% hemoglobin. The Greek SEKAP Bio-Filter
cigarette’s midfilter was also tested for possible changes in
carbonyl compound, CO and NO concentrations. Analyses are

ongoing. A memorandum on the coconut shell morphology of the Bio-
Filter cigarette’s midfilter was distributed ky 3. J. Craven.
